atbm6031: use a relative firmware loader name

request_firmware() expects a firmware name relative to the kernel firmware
search directories.  Passing /lib/firmware/atbm6031_fw.bin makes Linux 4.4
prepend /lib/firmware and probe the non-existent path
/lib/firmware//lib/firmware/atbm6031_fw.bin.

The package already installs the blob in /lib/firmware (through the /lib to
/usr/lib symlink), so request only its basename.

Signed-off-by: Matt Davis <matteius@gmail.com>

--- a/configs/atbm6031.config
+++ b/configs/atbm6031.config
@@ -62,10 +62,10 @@ CONFIG_ATBM_MODULE_PM_STAYAWK="pm_stayawake"
 CONFIG_ATBM_MODULE_DRIVER_NAME="atbm_wlan"
 CONFIG_ATBM_PLATFORM_DEVICE_NAME="atbm_dev_wifi"
 CONFIG_ATBM_SDIO_VID=0x007a
 CONFIG_ATBM_SDIO_PID=0x6011
 CONFIG_ATBM_MODULE_DRIVER_NAME="atbm6031"
 CONFIG_ATBM_MODULE_NAME="atbm6031"
-CONFIG_ATBM_FW_NAME="/lib/firmware/atbm6031_fw.bin"
+CONFIG_ATBM_FW_NAME="atbm6031_fw.bin"
 CONFIG_ATBM_CONFIG_FILE="/usr/share/wifi/atbm_txpwer_dcxo_cfg.txt"
 CONFIG_ATBM_RATE_POWER_CONFIG_FILE="/usr/share/wifi/set_rate_power.txt"
 CONFIG_MAC80211_ATBM_RC_DEFAULT=""
